<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[1]
Date: Sun, 6 Jul 2003
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Jerusalem Post online [edited]
<http://www.jpost.com/servlet/Satellite?pagename=JPost/A/JPArticle/ShowFull&cid=1057464260168>

2000 IAI workers out with flu-like symptoms
--------------------------------------------
2000 workers of the Israel Aircraft Industries plant in Lod stayed home on
Thu, 3 Jul 2002 -- and it wasn't industrial action. There were 60 absentees
on Wed, 2 Jul 2003.
All the missing workers told their bosses they had stomach aches and high
fever. The Ramle District Health Office sent inspectors to take samples of
cafeteria food and water from the plant in order to identify the source of
the illness. Results will be available soon. The inspectors ruled out the
possibility of environmental pollutants causing the illness. According to
the Health Ministry, none of the workers has been hospitalized.
[Byline: Judy Siegel-Itzkovich]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
